    "Takaya Awata is president and CEO of Tokyo-listed Toridoll Holdings, Japan's largest operator of noodle  restaurants.",
    "Awata opened his first yakitori grilled-chicken restaurant in 1985, after dropping out of the Kobe City University of Foreign Studies.",
    "Toridoll has 1,800 restaurants in Japan, China, Singapore, Europe. and the U.S.",
    "The company posted $1.2 billion in revenue in the fiscal year through March 2023. Toridoll plans to double its revenue over the next five years to $2 billion, with about 3,700 more restaurants.",
    "In October 2021, the firm listed its Tam Jai International, an operator of Chinese noodle restaurants that it acquired in 2018, on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange."
